<doc id="372393" wikidata="Q3006692" url="?curid=372393" title="Semiperfect magic cube">
<text>In mathematics, a semiperfect magic cube is a magic cube that is not a perfect magic cube, i.e., a magic cube for which the cross section diagonals do not necessarily sum up to the cube&#x27;s magic constant.

==References==</text><links>
